Parameter.Name: UseRecordHandlerStrategy
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will enable the commmon module use to process strategies.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixPublishFlatLegFields
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will publish flat leg fields for strategies such as wPriceLeg1, wPriceLeg2, etc. To use the RecordHandlerStrategy vector leg fields this should be turned off.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseStaggeringReconnect
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to true the feedhandler will manage the connecting/disconnecting to full refresh subfeeds, and allows only less than CmemdpFixManagerMaxConnectedSnapshots number of full refresh subfeeds conneced synchronizely.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixManagerCheckInterval
Parameter.Comment: This is the interval (milliseconds) for feedhandler to apply the logic of staggering joining, only actived when CmemdpFixUseStaggeringReconnect is true.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixManagerMaxConnectedSnapshots
Parameter.Comment: This is the maximal number of snapshot subfeeds being connected synchronizely, only activated when CmemdpFixUseStaggeringReconnect is true

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixAlwaysConnectToSnapshot
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter is set to true, the snapshot subfeeds are connected all the time.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixDisconnectSnapshotLimitTime
Parameter.Comment: Specifies the time limit, in seconds. The feed handler disconnects full refresh channels in this time limit after it recovers the current stale instruments to their current market status.

Parameter.Name: LineControllerUseOverridesExisting
Parameter.Comment: This should be set to true.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseBatchProcessing
Parameter.Comment: If this parameter set to false the feedhandler will handle the date entries individually, however, this can cause the transitory crossed/locked books.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixForceApplyConversionFactor
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feedhandler applies the conversion factor (defaulted/from exchange) no mattter the wFractionalFlag is on or off. This flag is only populated for some of cbot products.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixProcessTradingMode
Parameter.Comment: When set o true, the feedhandler populates the field of wTradingMode from TradingSessionId carried in bood update block.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixCalcOpenPrice
Parameter.Comment: When set to false, the feedhandler does not calculate the open price from the first trade message when the Opening Trade Message is not available

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixPublishIsinCode
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feedhandler populates the wIsinCode with the tag of 48 (SecurityID)

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixSettleDateTimeZone
Parameter.Comment: This can be set to the local time zone to get a proper wSettleDate,e.g US/Eastern

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixTradeFilter
Parameter.Comment: It is possible to apply a filter using this parameter to have finely grained control over which combinations of CME Trades to be published by the cmemdpfix feedhandler based on the contents of the wCrossTradeInd field (which is in turn generated from the wTradeCondition field). The filter will make use of the least significant nibble of the binary representation of the given unsigned integer to work out which trades to publish. The least significant (1st bit) represents a normal trade. the 2nd bit represents an implied trade, the 3rd an ExPit trade and the 4th bit represents Opening trades. Ergo, to publish, for instance, only Normal, ExPit and Opening trades the value of the parameter should be set to the integer 11 (1011 in binary). To publish, say, only Normal trades this value would be the integer 1 (0001 in binary). By default, it publishes all trades (1111 in binary)

Parameter.Name: StrategyMaxLegs
Parameter.Comment: In cme rlc feed, the number of the legs can be up to 40, however in fast/fix, theoretically, this can be unlimited.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixManagerExtraStaggeredLogging
Parameter.Comment: When set to false, the feedhandler logs less staggering events.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseDisplayFactorPerRootSymbol
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feedhandler applies the display factor per root symbol.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixDisplayFactorPerRootSymbolProducts
Parameter.Comment: It can be 0 - for Futures only, 1 - Futures and Options, 2 - all products (Futures+Options+Spreads), 3 - Options only, 4 - Options and Spreads only.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixDollarStrikePrice
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feedhandler does not applies the display factor on strike price, but take the raw price as cents, and publish it as dollar.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseConversionFactorForLegPrice
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feedhandler applies the conversion factor on the leg price fields. This feature can only be activated when another existed parameter - CmemdpFixUseSymbolForId=true, because, it is possible that when the security definition of a spread is available, the feed handler still has no information for its legs. By turning on CmemdpFixUseSymbolForId, the feed handler only process a spread when the definitons of its leg instruments are available already

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixFilteringUnexpectedSymbols
Parameter.Comment: When set to false, a definition channel will not filtering out those symbols actually published on other channels, which is possible for some test symbols.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixMaxAttemptsForLineSwitch
Parameter.Comment: When set to a non-zero value, the feed handler switches to the other (secondary/primary)line when the connecting attempts is greater than this value.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixSwitchLinesUponRequestReject
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feed handler switches to the other (secondary/primary)line upon receiving the message of request reject, i.e. fix message type = "Y".

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixDefSpoolingOn
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feed handler spools the definition messages, and disconnect the definition channels once all definition messages are received.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixProcessDefMsgsBatchSize
Parameter.Comment: The number of the definition messages being processed when the timer is triggered.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixProcessDefMsgsBatchInterval
Parameter.Comment: The time interval of batched processing, (milliseconds)

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseTwoDigitsYearSymbology
Parameter.Comment: When set to true, the feed handler generate two digits year symbology for Futures and Options

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixRollingRecordsAtEndOfSession
Parameter.Comment: When set to false, the feed handler does not roll the records upon receiving the status change of EndOfSession

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixLargeScaleGapThreshold
Parameter.Comment: The gap watermark of reconnecting to snapshot subfeeds, this is for the sequence number per either symbol or channel.

Parameter.Name: CmemdpFixUseTheoreticalSettlementType
Parameter.Comment: This should always be set to true for the theoretical settlement price using the logic in FF20ClImp.pdf (v1.6). Customers can still choose the logic in FF20ClImp.pdf (v1.5) or earlier by setting this parameter to false
